to create new database
-> use dbname
-> user nodej

to create new collection inside database
-> db.createCollection

to view all the collections inside the database
-> show collections

to insert single data at a time:
-> db.collectionname.insertone({vlaues})
-> db.userData.insertOne({name:'Test',email:'testing@gmail.com',phone:'1234567890'}) -> insert data

to insert many data at the same time
-> db.userData.insertMany([{name:'newuser',email:'newuser@gmail.com',phone:'12345'},{name:'currentuser',email:'currentuser@gmail.com',phone:'09876'}])

to find data
// return all the data available
-> db.collectionname.find()
-> db.userData.find()

to update data
// $set to update
// $-> to access the function
-> db.collectionname.updateOne({key},{$set:{newvalue}})
-> db.userData.updateOne({name:'currentuser'},{$set:{email:'changedcurrentuser@gmail.com'}})

to delete data
-> db.collectionname.deleteOne({key})
-> db.userData.deleteOne({name:'newuser'})

using mongodb://localhost:27017 as your mongodb url might give error
to fix it change localhost with 127.0.0.1 mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017

use await if output is giving promise pending

module: sends fragment of code/function isstead of whole file

